<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 08 at 11:20PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Anson
and Stanly Counties through 1215 AM EDT...
At 1119 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mt Pleasant, or 11 miles southeast of Downtown Concord, moving
southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and heavy rainfall.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Albemarle, Plyler, Locust, Oakboro, Stanfield and Finger.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
